is there an easy way to get the burrs out of my dogs hair she has long hair and is a golden retriever who likes to run in the woods in my back yard to cause minimal loss of hair and pain to the animal think of it as taking the hair out of the burr rather than taking the burr out of the hair hold the tangled burr between your index finger and thumb you should still be able to see a section of implicated hair between the burr and the dog's body take a comb and using just the end few teeth of the comb start to separate the hair from the burr a few hairs at a time until all the hair is freed and the burr is left in your hand do not bath the dog until the burrs have been removed it will cause more hair to become tangled in the burr and will tighten the knot Textile manufacturing Knife Drill bit Baldness Double bass Five Ks Violin Cello Dog Shen Gong Wu Niddah Archery Dreadlocks Hair Kodocha Hand Carpal tunnel syndrome Swimming Reamer Dog training Vice President of the United States Human Haircut German Shepherd Dog Pyrenean Shepherd Burr Redding Professional wrestling holds Beehive (beekeeping) Chucky Pancamo Erogenous zone Domestic rabbit Reservoir Dogs Bass guitar Three Stooges Mattress Hamster Shampoo Professional wrestling match types Obedience training Flanging U.S. Electoral College Textile manufacturing terminology Card scraper Keeshond Leaf Dog collar Bigfoot Thermoregulation Fox hunting Guqin Knot Diving Professional wrestling attacks Fitts' law Radiation therapy Breastfeeding Normal distribution Prostate cancer Baldness treatments RuneScape quests Sin City Clarinet American football Sento Joker (comics) Act Without Words II Timpani Anorexia nervosa Fishing Beard Aerial (dance move) Portuguese Water Dog The Descent of Man, and Selection in Relation to Sex Raymond Burr Nail (anatomy) Pitaten Red Dwarf characters Horizontal bar Penguin (comics) Burdock Sheepshank Glossary of climbing terms Drawing Gesture Cat Animal testing The Inside Harmonica Fancy rat Comb Phys